95011f4e-d48c-40d3-856f-5a4d81a06478	SustainAI Protein	Enhance research efficiency and innovation in sustainable protein production through a multi-agent AI framework leveraging fine-tuned Large Language Models (LLMs).	Current research in sustainable protein production is fragmented and reliant on manual processes, making it time-consuming and inefficient to access and analyze vast amounts of scientific literature. There is a need for an intelligent system that can efficiently retrieve and extract relevant data pertaining to microbial protein sources.	Creation of a multi-agent AI system focusing on literature search and information extraction specifically for microbial protein production. This includes the development of a user-friendly interface for researchers.	["Academic researchers in microbiology and protein production","Food technology companies","Agricultural researchers","Environmental science experts","Policy makers in sustainable food systems"]	The system consists of two main agents: a literature search agent that retrieves relevant papers based on user queries, and an information extraction agent that processes the retrieved literature to extract key biological and chemical data related to microbial protein sources. This is achieved through fine-tuning and prompt engineering of state-of-the-art LLMs for optimal performance.	The system architecture comprises an input query module (user interface), a literature search agent that utilizes the PubMed API for document retrieval, and an information extraction agent that uses GPT-based models. The outputs are harmonized and displayed in a dashboard for user analysis.	Utilization of dual optimization strategies (prompt engineering and fine-tuning) for LLMs tailored specifically for the extraction of information from scientific documents. The modular nature of the system allows for easy integration of additional agents and capabilities.	The system is designed to streamline the research process in sustainable prote