03b1c264-56bd-4974-ac45-50dcde370e7d	CoMind	Automate machine learning engineering by leveraging community knowledge, enhancing collaborative problem-solving, and producing innovative solutions in competitive environments.	Existing ML agents typically function in isolation, failing to utilize collective knowledge or engage with community insights, which are vital for improving solution quality. They often converge on repetitive strategies without innovation, limiting their performance in dynamic contexts.	Implementation of a collaborative agent for machine learning engineering tasks, able to access and utilize community contributions like discussions and shared code in structured competition environments. Suitability for tasks such as model selection, implementation, and reporting.	["Data scientists","Machine learning engineers","Research institutions","Organizations involved in data analysis competitions","Educational institutions teaching data science and machine learning"]	CoMind operates in iterative cycles consisting of four stages: Idea Selection, Idea Generation, Implementation and Improvement, and Report Generation. It leverages a shared knowledge pool comprising community insights and solutions, dynamically evolving its strategies based on performance feedback and discussions.	The system comprises a central agent module that coordinates tasks across four operational stages. It integrates an idea pool and report pool for maintaining shared resources while implementing an iterative workflow that utilizes feedback from past solutions and community insights.	CoMind introduces parallel exploration and iterative refinement of multiple solution drafts, allowing it to integrate new community knowledge dynamically. This process improves solution diversity and overcomes typical context limitations faced by isolated ML agents.	CoMind can be applied in data science competitions to automatically generate and refine machine learning models, leveraging community discussion