53a8ff0e-59a2-4b40-8518-1e6780e5e586	RAG Systems for Real-World Applications	To design, develop, and evaluate Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems that effectively utilize external knowledge to enhance accuracy, relevance, and user experience across diverse real-world domains.	Current AI implementations may lack factual accuracy and contextual relevance due to reliance on non-updated models and static data. RAG systems can address these issues by grounding LLMs in real-time external knowledge, yet their practical application and evaluation in varied domains remain underexplored.	Development of RAG systems across five specific domains: governance, cybersecurity, agriculture, industrial research, and medical diagnostics. Each system incorporates multilingual capabilities, semantic retrieval, and tailored LLMs based on the domain requirements.	["Local governments","Cybersecurity firms","Agricultural organizations","Industrial research institutes","Healthcare providers"]	Each RAG system includes two phases: a Retrieval Phase, where user queries are embedded and matched with relevant information from a vector database, and a Generation Phase, where these retrieved texts are combined with the user query and processed by a large language model to generate coherent, contextually relevant answers.	The system architecture consists of multiple core components: Data Sources (structured/unstructured documents), Vector Database (for storing knowledge in embeddings), Query Processing (tokenization and embedding generation), Preprocessing Pipelines (for OCR and web data extraction), and the communication layer to interface with users through a web-based interface or API responses.	The integration of multilingual OCR, domain-specific LLMs, and a local server or cloud-based deployment ensures systems are tailored for their intended applications. User-centered evaluations capture real-world performance aspects, offering insights into ease of use, relevance, and user trust, which are crucial for deploying AI systems in sensitive domains.	Each RAG system improves access to pertinent information for decision-making in their respective domains, such as querying municipal policy documents, understanding cyber threats, accessing agricultural best practices, retrieving engineering research, or providing clinical insights for medical diagnoses.	\N	2025-06-27 04:00:00+00	2025-06-27 04:00:00+00	[{"url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.20869", "title": "RAG Systems for Real-World Applications"}]	{"Tampere University","Disarm Foundation",AgriHubi,"FEMMa Consortium","Clinical Diagnostics Group"}
b036ccff-4b9f-41bd-9362-6e58ea5b8278	AbMEGD-AI	Enhance the efficiency and accuracy of antibody design against complex antigens using multi-scale equivariant graph diffusion models.	Current antibody design models struggle to effectively capture complex molecular interactions while preserving structural integrity and symmetries, leading to challenges in designing high-affinity antibodies for diverse antigens.	End-to-end framework for co-designing antibody sequences and structures. Focus on complex antigens with advanced geometric deep learning approaches for optimized binding affinity.	["Biotechnology companies","Pharmaceutical firms","Research institutions","Genomics and proteomics labs"]	The system employs multi-scale equivariant graph diffusion to optimize antibody sequences and structures. It integrates residue-level and atomic-level features, facilitating interactions that capture both local details and global structural behaviors essential for effective antigen-antibody binding.	The framework consists of modules for feature extraction (residue and atomic), multi-level representation, and diffusion-based generative modeling to ensure E(3)-equivariance throughout the design process, enabling accurate predictions for antibody binding affinities and improved antibody stability.	AbMEGD utilizes a unified generative framework that integrates geometric deep learning techniques, enhancing feature extraction with an innovative multi-scale approach, offering significant increases in amino acid recovery and overall structure accuracy compared to existing design models.	Pharmaceutical companies can leverage AbMEGD for rapid antibody design and optimization, significantly reducing time for therapeutic development and improving the efficacy of resulting antibody therapies in response to emerging pathogens.	\N	2025-06-27 04:00:00+00	2025-06-27 04:00:00+00	[{"url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.20957", "title": "AbMEGD-AI"}]	{"Wuhan University School of Computer Science","Macquar